<item>
            <title>[LU-16633] obd_get_mod_rpc_slot() is vulnerable to races</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16633</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;wait_woken() called from obd_get_mod_rpc_slot() resets WQ_FLAG_WOKEN flag, but leaves the corresponding wq_entry on the list.&lt;br/&gt;
__wake_up_locked_key() (called from obd_put_mod_rpc() in another thread) finds that wq_entry on the list w/o WQ_FLAG_WOKEN set, consumes one more slot (cl_mod_rpcs_in_flight++).&lt;br/&gt;
this way we leak slots.&lt;br/&gt;
this can be catched with sanity/182b.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
